verses.verse: Prayse the Lorde. Prayse the Lord (ye seruauntes) O prayse the name of the Lorde.
Blessed be the name of the Lorde, from thys tyme forth for euermore.
The Lordes name is praysed, from the risyng vp of the Sunne vnto the goynge downe of the same.
The Lord is hye aboue all Heathen, and his glory aboue the heauens.
Who is lyke vnto the Lorde oure God, that hath hys dwellyng so hye,
& yet humbleth him self, to behold the thynges that are in heauen & earth?
He taketh vp the simple out of the dust, and lyfteth the poore out of the myre.
That he maye sett him with the princes, euen with the prynces of his people.
He maketh the baren woman to kepe house, and to be a ioyfull mother of children. Prayse the Lorde.
